The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Dearborn, Michigan, Jan. 23: Ford Motor Co today said it would eliminate 25,000-30,000 jobs and close 14 plants in North America in a bid to staunch huge losses in its auto operations. The facilities, including seven vehicle assembly plants, will stop production by 2012. Ford said it hoped its hard-hitting plan would restore profitability in North America by 2008. The company hopes to save $6 billion by 2010. Unions have called it a Black Monday for workers .

 New Delhi, Jan. 23: The Union cabinet is likely to discuss tomorrow the recommendations of a group of ministers (GoM) on liberalising the FDI regime, including in the retail sector. The GoM?s suggestions include allowing 51 per cent foreign direct investment (FDI) in single branded retail and opening up five more sectors for FDI through the automatic route, official sources said. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 23: Bank of Baroda today said it has fixed the price for its public offering at Rs 230 a share, which would fetch Rs 1,633 crore. The offer was oversubscribed 12.70 times.

 New Delhi, Jan. 23: The government has formed a group of ministers to be chaired by defence minister Pranab Mukherjee for resolving issues related to spectrum. The group will suggest a spectrum pricing policy, examine the possibility of creating a spectrum reallocation fund and guidelines for operating the fund.

 New Delhi, Jan. 23: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will hold a meeting with exporters tomorrow in a bid to push up exports and expand trade engagement.

 Mumbai, Jan. 23: Hindustan Lever today said it has completed the transfer of its 100 per cent shareholding in Doom Dooma Tea Co to McLeod Russel India Ltd.

 New Delhi, Jan. 23: Vedanta Resources Plc will issue $850-million convertible bonds to repay debt and meet capital expenses for the smelter plant at Jharsuguda in Orissa.




